Ad Text:
We are seeking a highly motivated Supply Chain Analyst to join a thriving retail organisation in Woolloomooloo. This role involves analysing supply chain operations and implementing strategies to improve efficiency and cost-effectiveness.

Client Details

This opportunity is with a well-established retail organisation known for its robust operations and commitment to delivering exceptional service. As a part of a large organisation, this company focuses on maintaining operational excellence and fostering professional growth for its employees.

Description

Leverage data-driven insights to guide and enhance decision-making across the supply chain.
Build and maintain accurate demand forecasts to optimize inventory levels, maximize sales, and minimize waste.
Deliver network-wide analysis on forecast accuracy and identify opportunities for improvement.
Incorporate Limited Time Offers (LTO) and promotional forecasts into the MMX environment to support operational teams.
Lead initiatives to refine demand planning processes, including recommending adjustments to order quantities and allocations.
Analyze historical trends, seasonality, and market dynamics to improve forecast precision at both macro and site-specific levels.
Support strategic projects such as menu launches, promotional campaigns, and market expansion by providing actionable recommendations on order quantities and allocations.

Profile

* Bachelor's degree in engineering, business, Supply Chain, Information Technology, or a related field.

Minimum 3 years of professional experience in Supply Chain, Demand Planning, or Supply Planning (required).
Proven track record of supporting or managing demand planning or supply planning processes.
Proficiency in data analysis tools (Excel, or even SQL, Alteryx, Python/R etc)
Proficient in creating data visualizations and dashboards using tools like Power BI or Tableau

Job Offer

Very strong package.
Additional superannuation benefits and an 8% performance bonus.
Opportunity to work in a vibrant retail industry environment.
Supportive company culture with a focus on professional growth.

If you're ready to take the next step in your career as a Supply Chain Analyst, we encourage you to apply today!

To apply online please click the 'Apply' button below. For a confidential discussion about this role please contact Barry Mcgrory at +61386166237.

Join the change. Electrify your future!

We've been proudly Aussie since 1837, always finding new ways to innovate in energy and essential services. Now, we're moving towards a sustainable future through electrification and investing in renewable energy-and we'd like you to join us. Whether you're on-site, in the office, or somewhere in between, you'll find opportunities to grow your career here. You'll work with a team that's passionate about powering Australian lives, in a culture that values inclusivity, respect, and learning. Help us create a cleaner energy future, and we'll back you every step of the way as you build your career.


About the role

An exciting new opportunity has become available for a Business Analyst to join our Integrated Portfolio Planning division on a 12-month assignment.
The Trading Technology team is the primary interface between AGL Technology and Integrated Energy's Trading & Integrated Portfolio Planning teams, as well as the Wholesale Risk and Finance teams.

Working closely with the Physical Markets Team who are responsible for managing AGL's electricity and gas procurement position. You will facilitate system and process changes and improvements that enable the Trading team to respond quickly to the market conditions and optimize the execution of physical trading strategies.


Key responsibilities

Business process mapping of complex systems and stakeholder dependencies
Supporting the analysis and requirements gathering process for front end development and data intensive products.
Implementation of complex engineering methodology and market rules to optimise physical trading outcomes across physical power, gas and FCAS markets.
Run and facilitate workshops to gather and document requirements for both business and technical stakeholders.
Analyse existing systems and processes to identify impacts, changes and opportunities.
Build and manage stakeholder relationships with a variety of different business units.
Assist delivery teams with the coordination of planning ceremonies.


About you

You are an established Business Analyst with a user-centered mindset who is comfortable with building relationships with a wide range of stakeholders ranging from delivery teams to senior leaders. Your ability to successfully map complex business processes and understand the 'bigger picture' of how systems interact will ensure your success in this role.

In addition to the above you will demonstrate:

Experience working to deliver complex initiatives end-to-end in an agile environment.
Experience applying different techniques to elicit business requirements.
Ability to balance multiple competing priorities and effectively manage expectations.
Excellent communication skills, both written and oral.
Ability to facilitate workshops to drive outcomes and solve problems between multiple parties.
Experience working with energy trading organisational functions such as trading (Forward, physical, origination) & an understanding of the Australian energy markets and emerging challenges are highly regarded.


Applications close Sunday 7 December 2025


Inclusion at AGL

At AGL, we value diversity and welcome applicants from various backgrounds, including Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander peoples, individuals with disabilities, culturally diverse individuals, and members of the LGBTQ+ community. AGL is dedicated to maintaining a diverse workforce and encourages applicants to share their lived experiences.
We offer reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process and respect the privacy of those who choose not to disclose. To learn more visit: www.agl.com.au/careers

AGL is proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer for All Women.

Our pre-employment screening process includes a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check and a medical assessment if necessary.
The information provided as part of your application to AGL will be managed in accordance with the AGL Privacy Policy.
AGL does not accept agency submissions unless approval has been granted by a member of the Talent Acquisition team. Candidates submitted by an agency without approval will not be considered by AGL.

Our global client is seeking an experienced Finance Data Governance Manager to support a major Defence program and help strengthen a governed, data-driven finance environment. This role suits someone who enjoys working across finance processes, data governance, documentation and senior stakeholder engagement within a structured organisation. Baseline Security clearance required. 

About the role
You will contribute to uplifting finance governance capability for a large Defence client. Working within an established governance and technical team, you will produce high-quality documentation and frameworks that support financial operations, data integrity and organisational compliance.
This position is suited to someone who is adaptable, detail-oriented and confident interacting with senior Defence stakeholders.

What you’ll be doing
• Developing and maintaining Defence-aligned finance governance artefacts
• Producing Data Management Agreements, Privacy Impact Assessments, Finance Object Reference Guides, operating procedures and executive-level reports
• Supporting all finance governance and data governance tasks across the program
• Interpreting and documenting finance processes, controls, data flows and requirements
• Working closely with technical and governance teams to ensure accuracy, consistency and compliance
• Engaging senior client stakeholders to clarify requirements, review deliverables and support decisions
Skills and experience we’re looking for
• Baseline security clearance is essential
• Experience in finance governance, financial operations, or financial documentation
• Working knowledge of SAP S/4HANA Finance (FI/CO) is preferred
• Experience in Defence, government or consulting environments is advantageous
• Comfortable authoring documents for senior executives and operating in evolving environments
• Ability to produce Tier 2/4 style documentation including SOPs, QRGs, visual guides and executive summaries
• Strong skills in Excel, Word and PowerPoint
• Accounting background is helpful but not mandatory

Team and environment
You will join a delivery team of technical specialists and governance professionals. Reporting to the Engagement Lead, you will work alongside managers and senior consultants across finance, SAP and governance workstreams.

Who this role suits
Candidates with backgrounds in Defence finance teams, finance transformation, SAP finance, finance data governance, financial policy, government consulting or similar domains. Minimum of Baseline Security clearance is required for this role.

Data Science & AI Manager

So…who are we?

Techtronic Industries (TTI) is a global powerhouse in consumer and professional products, leading the way in the home improvement and construction industries. Our brand portfolio includes household names like RYOBI, AEG, Hoover, Vax, Kango, and Empire - trusted by tradies and DIYers across the globe.

We're not just about tools. We're about innovation, insights, and impact. At TTI, you'll be part of a culture that values curiosity, collaboration, and continuous growth. We're here to help you thrive - and make a real difference.





About the role

We're looking for a Data Science & AI Manager to lead the charge in transforming data into strategic advantage. Reporting to our Head of Insights, you'll shape the vision, lead high-impact analytics projects, and drive AI innovation across our consumer business.

You'll manage a team of BI Developers, mentor future data leaders, and work closely with stakeholders to turn complex data into clear, actionable insights. This is a role for someone who's equal parts strategist, technologist, and storyteller.





Advanced Analytics & Innovation


Design and deploy scalable AI/ML models
Write clean, efficient code using Python, R, SQL, and cloud platforms (AWS, Azure)
Stay ahead of emerging tech and integrate it into business solutions
Champion ethical AI practices and ensure data quality and compliance

Strategic Leadership


Develop and deliver the advanced analytics roadmap
Advise senior leaders and translate business goals into data opportunities
Prioritise high-impact initiatives based on ROI and feasibility

Stakeholder Engagement


Build strong relationships across the business
Translate complex models into compelling stories for non-technical audiences
Collaborate cross-functionally to align data strategies with business needs

Team Leadership


Lead and mentor BI Developers and Data Specialists
Foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning
Support agile delivery and resource planning

What we're looking for

You're a data visionary with a hands-on approach. You love solving problems, leading teams, and making data meaningful. Here's what you'll bring:

✔️ 5+ years in analytics, data science, or consulting
✔️ Bachelor's or Master's in Data Science, Computer Science, or related field
✔️ Proven experience with ML/AI in strategic business contexts
✔️ Strong Python skills and cloud platform experience (AWS, Azure, GCP)
✔️ Familiarity with frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn
✔️ Experience with QlikSense (preferred), Tableau, or Power BI
✔️ Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills
✔️ A passion for ethical AI and continuous improvement





What we can offer you


Hybrid working
Wellbeing Hub + EAP support
Generous product discounts
Recognition programs and team celebrations
Learning and development opportunities
Paid parental leave, and more!



If you're ready to lead the future of data and AI at TTI, STOP… look no further and APPLY NOW!

Greenfield Project Finance Business Partner
Location: Sydney  
Industry: FMCG / Manufacturing
Employment Type: Permanent
Contact: ajblyth@sharpandcarter.com.au

Key requirements for this role: 

Strong financial modelling skillset 
Prior exposure to a significant CAPEX project/transformation programme
CA/CPA qualification
SME FMCG/manufacturing or construction industry exposure, ideally in factory based environments/exposure

About the Business
A proudly Australian success story, my client is a private-equity backed organisation renowned for its manufacturing, innovation, and commitment to quality. The business is entering an exciting new phase of growth, underpinned by a significant capital investment — the development of a new, state-of-the-art manufacturing facility.

As part of this transformation, my client is seeking to appoint a commercially astute finance business partner to play a pivotal role in supporting the financial management of this major initiative.

Key Duties & Responsibilities
Working closely with the various key stakeholders including the CFO and broader leadership team, your responsibilities will include:

Partnering with senior stakeholders to translate complex financial data into clear insights and recommendations.
Developing and presenting business cases and scenario modelling to support high-impact decision making (often requiring quick turnaround, operating 'in the grey' from partial data)
Monitoring and managing project expenditure against approved budgets, forecasts, and cash flow.
Ensuring the accuracy, control and integrity of project financials, invoices and supplier contracts.
Preparing executive-level financial reports and PowerPoint presentations for the SteerCo and Board.
Providing the right financial information to the right people — tailoring insight to the audience for maximum impact.
Supporting project governance and compliance with strong financial discipline and attention to detail.
About You
You’ll be a dynamic and resourceful finance professional who thrives in a fast-paced, project-based environment. You’ll combine analytical rigour with commercial storytelling — able to distil data into meaningful narratives that influence decisions at the most senior level.

You will bring:

CA/CPA (or equivalent) qualification with minimum 5 years' experience in a comparable finance role.
Proven exposure to large-scale capital or transformation projects.
Strong financial modelling and scenario analysis capability, with the ability to work with incomplete or evolving data at pace
Excellent communication and presentation skills — confident preparing Board-ready packs and engaging with non-financial stakeholders.
Tech-savvy mindset with a focus on efficiency and automation rather than manual processes (including PowerBI)
A collaborative, pragmatic approach with strong commercial acumen and attention to detail.
What’s in it for You

This is a rare opportunity to join a highly respected Australian brand at a defining moment in its growth story. You’ll play a central role in a hugely significant investment, helping shape the future of its operations and long-term success.

You’ll work alongside an exceptional leadership team in a culture that values creativity, collaboration and authenticity. This is a role where your insight will genuinely influence outcomes, and where you’ll see your work make a tangible impact.

How to Apply

To confidentially discuss this opportunity, please click Apply or contact Aj Blyth at ajblyth@sharpandcarter.com.au.

Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
The Department of Local Government, Water and Volunteers (DLGWV) is at the forefront of driving sustainable growth across Queensland. Our mission is to manage water resources responsibly and empower councils to support and grow Queensland communities. With over 700 dedicated professionals across Brisbane and regional offices, we work tirelessly to ensure that Queensland's communities, businesses, and water resources thrive.

The Role

This role will focus on developing and improving a robust Data and Information Management Governance Framework, managing risks to data holdings and the information assets of the department, and ensuring the ongoing supportability of information systems. This includes leading the department's response to audit findings, fostering a culture of information awareness, and driving continuous improvement in data and information governance practices.

About You

There are no mandatory requirements for this role, however the following would be highly regarded:

- experience in applying data and information governance frameworks such as DMBoK.

- implementing information management initiatives utilising the M365 suite.

- Prince2® Project Management training or equivalent experience in a project environment.

- Qualifications or experience in Agile Methodologies.

The Benefits

Opportunities for professional development and leadership growth.
A respectful, inclusive workplace that values diversity and encourages collaboration.
Access to Queensland Government employee benefits and programs.

DLGWV is committed to respecting, protecting and promoting human rights in our decision-making and actions. We value the diversity of our workforce and are guided by the Queensland Public Sector Inclusion and Diversity Strategy. We strive to create a respectful and rewarding workplace culture that encourages, recognises and embraces every individual's contribution within a collaborative environment that allows all employees to thrive.

How to Apply: Submit your resume and cover letter (1 to 2 page) demonstrating your suitability for the position.

This position is available at the following locations: Brisbane or Flexible

Please advise your preference with your application.

Applications to remain current for 12 months

Job Title: Senior Manager Risk Culture and Capability
Ad Text:
Step into a high-impact role where your vision shapes enterprise-wide risk capability, drives cultural change, and positions you as a trusted advisor to executive leadership.

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As the Senior Manager, Risk Culture & Capability at Australian Retirement Trust, you’ll be at the forefront of shaping and embedding a high-performing risk culture across the organisation. Reporting to the General Manager, you’ll lead the design and delivery of innovative frameworks and programs that drive strong risk behaviours, clear accountability, and uplift capability at every level. This is a high-impact, strategic role where you’ll partner with senior leaders, influence mindsets, and ensure ART not only meets but exceeds regulatory expectations. If you’re passionate about culture transformation and thrive in a dynamic, values-driven environment, this is your opportunity to make a lasting difference.




Key aspects of the role include:

Lead the development and implementation of ART’s enterprise-wide Risk Culture Strategy and Framework.
Design and deliver targeted risk capability uplift programs for leaders and staff.
Champion a values-aligned, transparent risk culture in partnership with executive and frontline leaders.
Conduct risk culture assessments using qualitative and quantitative methods.
Define and report on key risk culture metrics to senior leadership and Board committees.
Collaborate with People & Impact to embed risk capability into talent and leadership programs.
Act as a trusted advisor to the Chief Risk Officer and executive team on culture, governance, and accountability.
Ensure all initiatives align with APRA standards and regulatory expectations.
Build and lead a high-performing team of Risk Culture Specialists.
Drive continuous improvement through data-driven insights and stakeholder feedback.

This role is a permanent opportunity based in Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Proven experience designing and delivering culture, leadership, or capability uplift initiatives in complex organisations.
Strong expertise in developing and using culture measurement tools, surveys, and behavioural diagnostics.
Demonstrated ability to lead and develop high-performing teams, fostering collaboration and professional growth.
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and influencing skills, with a track record of partnering with executive leaders and cross-functional teams.
Deep understanding of risk management principles, APRA prudential standards (especially SPS 220 and SPS 510), and regulatory expectations.
Advanced analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data, identify trends, and provide actionable insights.
Outstanding written and verbal communication skills, including experience presenting to Boards and senior executives.
Strategic thinker with the ability to translate vision into practical, enterprise-wide implementation plans.
Experience collaborating with HR, L&D, and business leaders on people and culture strategies.
Relevant tertiary and/or post-graduate qualifications in risk management, organisational psychology, business, or a related field (highly regarded).

About us

Our 2.4 million members trust us to take care of over $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close 7th December 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Job Title: Senior Manager Risk Governance, Systems & Insights
Ad Text:
Championing strategic clarity and innovation, you’ll shape the future of risk management by integrating cutting-edge technology, fostering collaboration, and delivering actionable insights that keep Australian Retirement Trust ahead of industry standards and regulatory expectations.

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As Senior Manager, Risk Governance, Systems & Insights, you will play a pivotal leadership role in shaping the risk management landscape at Australian Retirement Trust. You’ll be responsible for designing, implementing, and continuously enhancing risk frameworks, systems, and enterprise reporting that support informed decision-making at the highest levels. Our Data Engineering Team is comprised of data experts. We build world-class data solutions and applications that power crucial business decisions throughout the organisation. We manage multiple analytical data models and pipelines across Atlassian, covering finance, growth, product analysis, customer analysis, sales and marketing, and so on. We maintain Atlassian's data lake that provide a unified way of analysing our customers, our products, our operations, and the interactions among them.

We're hiring a Senior Data Engineer, reporting to the Data Engineering Manager based in Sydney. Here, you'll enable a world-class engineering practice, drive the approach with which we use data, develop backend systems and data models to serve the needs of insights, and help build Atlassian's data-driven culture. You love thinking about the ways the business can consume data and then figuring out how to build it

Working at Atlassian

Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity.

You'll partner with the product analytics and data scientist team to build the data solutions that allow them to obtain more insights from our data and use that to support important business decisions.

You'll work with different stakeholders to understand their needs and architect/build the data models, data acquisition/ingestion processes and data applications to address those requirements.

You'll add new sources, code business rules, and produce new metrics that support the product analysts and data scientists.

You'll be the data domain expert who understand all the nitty-gritty of our products.

You'll own a problem end-to-end. Requirements could be vague, and iterations will be rapid

You'll improve data quality by using & improving internal tools/frameworks to automatically detect DQ issues.

A BS in Computer Science or equivalent experience with 5+ years of professional experience as a Sr. Data Engineer or in a similar role.

Strong programming skills using Python

Working knowledge of relational databases and query authoring (SQL).

Experience designing data models for optimal storage and retrieval to meet product and business requirements.

Experience building scalable data pipelines using Spark (SparkSQL) with Airflow scheduler/executor framework or similar scheduling tools.

Experience working with AWS data services or similar Apache projects (Spark, Flink, Hive, and Kafka).

Understanding of Data Engineering tools/frameworks and standards to improve the productivity and quality of output for Data Engineers across the team.

Well versed in modern software development practices (Agile, TDD, CICD)

Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and wellbeing resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits.
